==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Youngling
<hw>Young"ling</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>geongling</ets>.]</ety> <def>A young person; a youth; also, any
animal in its early life.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧More dear . . . than
<xex>younglings</xex> to their dam.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He will not be so willing, I think, to join with you as with us
<qex>younglings</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Ridley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Youngling</ent>⟦br⟧

